  <section class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Local service</p>
    <h2>Research Chimney Sweep and Wood Heater Cleaning</h2>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>Research sits at the northern edge of Eltham, where the suburban fringe transitions into the Nillumbik Green Wedge — one of Melbourne's most significant bushland preservation zones. Properties here are mostly on large blocks with established native gardens, and the leafy corridor along Reynolds Road is some of the most densely vegetated residential land in the north-east. The elevated position and tree canopy create cold, still winter mornings, and wood heating is essential for most households from April through September. Nesting birds — particularly rosellas, Indian mynas and the occasional parrot — regularly occupy chimney pots over spring, and we clear nests in Research every autumn as a matter of course. Many properties have fireplaces from the 1960s and 1970s development period that haven't been cleaned in years.</p>
      <p>We also cover nearby areas such as {nearbySuburbs.map((item) => item.label).join(", ")}.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

